{"submission_id":"sub_069abef1782e90c8","run_id":"2026-06-20T13-20-29-520Z_1885472-ee6bcfea_ingest_meeting-doc-128906","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T13:59:59.463Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:069abef1782e90c85545b28c7e14ceff52dff808dbe547c090b22c0298e7161f","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_128906_shuttle_service_desc","label":"Employer-Based Shuttle service description","raw_text":"On June 1, 1997, Metro-North and WCDPW&T entered into an agreement for WCDPW&T to operate and Metro-North to partially subsidize the Employer-Based Shuttles that provide connecting bus service to and from Metro-North train stations serving the corporate parks along Westchester Avenue and Routes 119 and 120 in Westchester County...","payload":{"claim_text":"The Employer-Based Shuttles provide connecting bus service to and from Metro-North train stations serving the corporate parks along Westchester Avenue and Routes 119 and 120 in Westchester County, with the goals of increasing ridership on Metro-North trains and promoting public transportation. Most of the source of the ridership originates from Metro-North stations in the Bronx, and these shuttles provide a service for reverse commuters with employment in the County.","description":"Description of the Employer-Based Shuttle service including routes served and purpose"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_128906#p001_c0011","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_128906/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0011","text_sha256":"sha256:ddb8964ff98d5862b71774214a51ca22392c3eb9490dc8eb325e56fcc1376a96","text_source":"raw_text","role":"discussion"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_6cb84ca4cc23caee","run_id":"2026-06-20T13-20-29-520Z_1885472-ee6bcfea_ingest_meeting-doc-128906","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T14:00:17.963Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:6cb84ca4cc23caeef2f210f2c2205cbfe31e85e18cb414ccd3474822ac784d9d","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_128906_marketing_rationalization","label":"Marketing and rationalization plans","raw_text":"Metro-North intends to engage its marketing partners to further publicize these shuttles to increase ridership. In addition, Metro-North will be working with Westchester County to rationalize the connecting services with the goal of recommending different alternatives after 2024.","payload":{"claim_text":"Metro-North intends to engage its marketing partners to further publicize these shuttles to increase ridership. In addition, Metro-North will be working with Westchester County to rationalize the connecting services with the goal of recommending different alternatives after 2024.","description":"Future plans for marketing and service rationalization of the Employer-Based Shuttles"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_128906#p001_c0011","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_128906/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0011","text_sha256":"sha256:ddb8964ff98d5862b71774214a51ca22392c3eb9490dc8eb325e56fcc1376a96","text_source":"raw_text","role":"discussion"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_85aa2dba2fbe0b0b","run_id":"2026-06-20T13-20-29-520Z_1885472-ee6bcfea_ingest_meeting-doc-128906","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T14:00:37.555Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:85aa2dba2fbe0b0bbc91a2631e6be7d87ad8969a972db2a004825e822d76dd5a","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_128906_payment_reason","label":"FY2022 payment inadvertently not paid due to pandemic","raw_text":"Metro-North seeks authorization to make a past due payment for FY2022 in the amount of $58,413.60, which payment was inadvertently not paid as a consequence of the global pandemic and the lack of an amendment covering FY2022.","payload":{"claim_text":"The past due payment for FY2022 was inadvertently not paid as a consequence of the global pandemic and the lack of an amendment covering FY2022.","description":"Explanation for why the FY2022 payment was not paid"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_128906#p001_c0011","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_128906/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0011","text_sha256":"sha256:ddb8964ff98d5862b71774214a51ca22392c3eb9490dc8eb325e56fcc1376a96","text_source":"raw_text","role":"discussion"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_d8805d5162db6f17","run_id":"2026-06-20T13-20-29-520Z_1885472-ee6bcfea_ingest_meeting-doc-128906","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T14:00:56.312Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:d8805d5162db6f1717a28589e59e17d0beafbfab44cc7d05ae6d1cf12a6d21a2","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_128906_flat_rate_budget","label":"Flat rate budget impact","raw_text":"The flat rate established for the Employer-Based Shuttles provides Metro-North Railroad with a predictable yearly WCDPW&T payment which is included in its Operating Budget. The shuttle buses serve to increase railroad ridership and promote reverse commutation.","payload":{"claim_text":"The flat rate established for the Employer-Based Shuttles provides Metro-North Railroad with a predictable yearly WCDPW&T payment which is included in its Operating Budget. The shuttle buses serve to increase railroad ridership and promote reverse commutation.","description":"Budget impact description for the shuttle agreement"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_128906","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_128906#p001_c0013","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_128906/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0013","text_sha256":"sha256:e07064b5a854545ef34c3b05c28b32e56c6bdb878fe7219aaae8229341871c56","text_source":"raw_text","role":"budget_impact"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
